Deng Xiaoping funeral committee announced 
The funeral committee for Deng Xiaoping, who died Wednesday night, has
already been selected with President Jiang Zemin as its chairman, the
official Xinhua news agency said.
The committee contains 459 members and includes all top government and
party leaders, the news agency said early Thursday.
The top 10 members are Jiang, Premier Li Peng, assembly president Qiao
Shi, consultative assembly president Li Ruihuan, 95-year-old
revolutionary Peng Zhen, economic tzar Zhu Rongji, vice chairman of the
Central Military Commission Liu Huaqing, the "baby" of the politburo Hu
Jintao, Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren, and propaganda supremo Ding
Guangen.
No date was given for the funeral and Xinhua did not specify if Deng
would be buried or cremated.
